  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ghana house of refuge construction project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">House of refuge re-construction to provide a safe accommodation for pregnant and other vulnerable teenage girls living on the streets of Accra. Young street connected girls will also be provided with skills training to enable them start their own business or get employment. This project is being implemented by our local partner Street Girls Aid. A total of 145 Girls are expected to be housed and given training each year. The project will project temporal shelter to targeted pregnant teenagers, feeding, provide them antenatal services till delivery. Other services will include skills training for young girls in hair dressing, dress making, baking etc.</narrative>
  </description>
